6000|$|... "Dear father," [...] {{the letter}} ran, [...] "Bartley and I are married. We were married an hour ago, {{just across the}} New Hampshire line, by the Rev. Mr. Jessup. Bartley wants I should let you know the very first thing. I am going to Boston with Bartley to-night, and, {{as soon as we}} get settled there, I will write again. I want you should forgive us both; but if you wont forgive Bartley, you mustn't forgive me. You were mistaken about Bartley, <b>and</b> <b>I</b> <b>was</b> <b>right.</b> Bartley has told me everything, and I am {{perfectly}} satisfied. Love to mother.|$|E
